Name: DiscriminatorNetwork
Description: Protocol to use a discriminator network to calculate the error of the network being trained.

Properties.Name: discriminatorNetwork
Properties.Description: A built network that is used to approximate error.

Properties.Name: discriminatorNetworkOutputNodes
Properties.Description: A list of discriminatorNetwork nodes used for the error calculation.

Properties.Name: errorFunction
Properties.Description: Error function used to compute error between discriminatorNetwork output values and Y.
